\\nI’m considering the need for dynamic coverage with Class#forName from the constructor. It looks like I should use getDeclaredMethod from the constructor, while Method#invoke will be from gauge.value. So that's good. I see that the call to `Gauge.builder(... x -> invoke(...))` indicates that the value is invoked lazily, which seems like a smart choice. Now, I need to focus on writing this out effectively.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_tIuN8Rmxl3Jv559OgGHMVKaQ|fc_01d1283982501e62016a41dd36c45c8195aac59eb0baede611", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/src/test/java/io_micrometer/micrometer_core/FileDescriptorMetricsTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io_micrometer.micrometer_core;\n\nimport java.util.Collections;\n\nimport io.micrometer.core.instrument.Gauge;\nimport io.micrometer.core.instrument.Tag;\nimport io.micrometer.core.instrument.binder.system.FileDescriptorMetrics;\nimport io.micrometer.core.instrument.simple.SimpleMeterRegistry;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class FileDescriptorMetricsTest {\n    @Test\n    void bindsAndSamplesFileDescriptorGauges() {\n        SimpleMeterRegistry registry = new SimpleMeterRegistry();\n        try {\n            FileDescriptorMetrics fileDescriptorMetrics = new FileDescriptorMetrics(\n                    Collections.singleton(Tag.of(\"source\", \"test\")));\n\n            fileDescriptorMetrics.bindTo(registry);\n\n            Gauge openFiles = registry.find(\"process.files.open\").tag(\"source\", \"test\").gauge();\n            Gauge maxFiles = registry.find(\"process.files.max\").tag(\"source\", \"test\").gauge();\n\n            assertThat(openFiles).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(maxFiles).isNotNull();\n\n            double openFileCount = openFiles.value();\n            double maxFileCount = maxFiles.value();\n\n            assertThat(Double.isNaN(openFileCount)).isFalse();\n            assertThat(Double.isNaN(maxFileCount)).isFalse();\n            assertThat(openFileCount).isGreaterThanOrEqualTo(0.0);\n            assertThat(maxFileCount).isGreaterThanOrEqualTo(openFileCount);\n        } finally {\n            registry.close();\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 643, "output": 860, "cacheRead": 19456, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20959, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782701359840, "responseId": "resp_01d1283982501e62016a41dd305b6c8195b125f6d49eb00812"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_tIuN8Rmxl3Jv559OgGHMVKaQ|fc_01d1283982501e62016a41dd36c45c8195aac59eb0baede611", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1713 bytes to tests/src/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/src/test/java/io_micrometer/micrometer_core/FileDescriptorMetricsTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1782701368683}]}
